1. In the Shower¬†
With the pads of your 3 middle fingers, check the entire breast and armpit area pressing down with light, medium and firm pressure. 
Do this for both breasts to feel for any lump, thickening, hardened knot, or any breast changes.
#BreastCancerAwarenessMonth https://t.co/mz0QnpCwWk

3. Lying Down
When lying down,the breast tissue spreads out evenly along the chest wall. Using your hands,move the pads of your fingers around your breasts gently covering the entire breast area and armpit to check for discharge and lumps. #BreastCancerAwarenessMonth https://t.co/2mUgeJQBsx

If you find a lump, schedule an appointment with your doctor. However, 8 out of 10 lumps are not cancerous. 
For additional peace of mind, call your doctor whenever you have concerns.

Breast self-exam

A breast self-exam is a check-up a woman does at home to look for changes or problems in the breast tissue. Many women feel that doing this is important to their health.

#MayorHealth 
#BreastCancer 
#BreastCancerAwareness 
#BreastCancerAwarenessMonth

The best time to do a monthly self-breast exam is about 3 to 5 days after your period starts. Do it at the same time every month. Your breasts are not as tender or lumpy at this time in your monthly cycle

RT @MayorHealth: The best time to do a monthly self-breast exam is about 3 to 5 days after your period starts. Do it at the same time every month. Your breasts are not as tender or lumpy at this time in your monthly cycle

Recently we spoke w/ Dr. Alexandridis about the difference between a screening & a diagnostic mammogram?
Screening mammogram is used to screen for breast cancer. The patient has no symptoms, palpable mass or biopsy and is an average risk person
#ProjectPink #BreastCancer

Diagnostic mammograms are used when there is something we are looking for, a palpable mass found, or benign lesion removed in the last couple of years.  
This type of mammogram looks at the area in question, & there may be more than one picture taken. #ProjectPink #breastcancer https://t.co/3v2Kl9v2JA
